The paper deals with the optimal mechanism for differential privacy, which is a topic in cryptography and security (cs.CR). It also involves probability distributions and optimization, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the generalization of the mechanism to discrete query output settings and more abstract settings, which could fall under data structures (cs.DS) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
